snippet.title: Grimes Claps Back At Elon Musk For Correcting Explanation Of Son's Name
snippet.description:
Here's some important advice: If you're a dad, never correct your partner's misspellings just after she's given birth. Elon Musk found that out when he tried to correct his beau after she misspelled their newborn baby's name on Twitter.

The couple, who started dating in May 2018, welcomed a son together on May 4, 2020. Given the fact that they named him "X Æ A-12 Musk," some confusion regarding the announcement was bound to happen.

Yes, X Æ A-12 Musk. That’s the name of their son, and Grimes explained that the "A-12" portion is inspired by the couple's favorite aircraft, the SR-17. That, as it turns out, wasn't quite right -- and Elon Musk wasted no time in pointing Grimes' mistake out on Twitter.

Come find out more about why and how Grimes clapped back the origin of their child’s name.

#Grimes #ElonMusk #Celeb

Read full article: https://www.nickiswift.com/207847/grimes-claps-back-at-elon-musk-for-correcting-explanation-of-sons-name/
